.TH WXFREECELL 6 2026-04-19 "wxFreeCell 1.0" "Games"
.SH NAME
wxFreeCell \- Microsoft FreeCell solitaire card game
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B wxFreeCell
.RI [ file ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B wxFreeCell
is a wxWidgets port of the classic Microsoft FreeCell solitaire card
game.  The objective is to move all 52 cards to the four home cells,
building up each suit from ace to king.
.PP
The playing field consists of four
.B free cells
(temporary single-card holders) in the upper-left, four
.B home cells
(foundation piles) in the upper-right, and eight
.B columns
where the deck is dealt face up.
.SH RULES
Cards in the columns are stacked in descending order with alternating
colors (red on black, black on red).  Only one card at a time may be
moved, but free cells and empty columns may be used as temporary
storage to move groups of cards.  Any card may be placed in an empty
free cell; cards placed on the home cells must be the next in suit.
.SH KEYBOARD
Enable Num Lock to use the numeric keypad.
.TP
.B 0
Cycle through cards in the free cells.
.TP
.B 1\-8
Select the bottom card (or stack) of the numbered column.  Press the
same number again to cancel the selection.
.TP
.B 9
Move the selected card to its home cell.
.SH MENU COMMANDS
The
.B Game
menu provides New Game, Select Game (by number), Restart, Undo,
Statistics and Exit.  The
.B Options
menu toggles display preferences.  The
.B Help
menu opens this documentation.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/wxfreecell/wxfreecell.chm
Compiled HTML Help file shipped with the game.
.TP
.I /usr/share/applications/wxfreecell.desktop
Freedesktop application entry.
.TP
.I /usr/share/icons/hicolor/*/apps/wxfreecell.*
Application icons at multiple resolutions.
